Just documenting the way I setup my working environment for Django 1.4 on Dreamhost.



Django needs to be installed using virtualenv, since mine is a shared hosting account. Found the instructions for installing virtualenv at [1].



wget http://pypi.python.org/packages/source/v/virtualenv/virtualenv-1.7.1.2.tar.gz



tar xzf virtualenv-1.7.1.2.tar.gz

python virtualenv-1.7.1.2/virtualenv.py $HOME/env



 



 



 



